{"type":"message","id":"b7739db6","parentId":"1e9b89f0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:40:45.883Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qbx15m22yzh7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 083916\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the situation:\r\n\r\n1. Breakaway is a stateless discontinuous agent\r\n2. Current focus: Phase 1 Advancement - COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. Next action: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n4. Need to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy and predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe immediate next action from the Phase 1 advancement section is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLet me check if there's a `logs/` directory with pulse files. I should look at the current directory structure and recent pulse logs to understand what I'm working with.\r\n\r\nSince I need to implement the TIC classifier, I should:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs to understand their format\r\n2. Create a script or document that implements the TIC classifier approach\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take this pulse:\r\n- I could create a Python script that implements the TIC classifier\r\n- I could create documentation/specification for the TIC approach\r\n- I could analyze the existing pulse logs to understand patterns\r\n\r\nGiven the constraint to make one concrete action, I should probably:\r\n1. First look at the logs directory to see what pulse files exist\r\n2. Then create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nActually, I need to be careful - I'm supposed to do ONE concrete action that advances goals. Looking at the goal structure, I need to implement the TIC classifier. \r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating a Python script to classify pulse logs. The key steps will involve developing a systematic approach to identifying temporal invariants in the existing pulse files. I'll need to design a classifier that can accurately distinguish between variable and constant content across different pulse logs.\r\n\r\nMy implementation strategy will prioritize creating a modular, adaptable script that can handle the nuanced requirements of temporal invariance detection. This means developing algorithms that can recognize patterns and predict potential variations in pulse content.\r\n\r\nI'll verify the available log files and confirm the project directory structure before proceeding with the script development. Checking the logs directory will help me understand the data context and ensure the TIC classifier is appropriately configured.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement. I need to examine the existing pulse logs and implement the classifier to test the hypothesis that causal structure equals invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nList the logs directory to see available pulse files, then create the TIC classifier implementation script to begin testing invariant/variant classification on recent pulses.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef get_pulse_files() -> List[Path]:\r\n    \"\"\"Get all pulse log files sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for f in LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"):\r\n        match = PULSE_PATTERN.match(f.name)\r\n        if match:\r\n            pulses.append((match.group(1), f))\r\n    pulses.sort(key=lambda x: x[0])\r\n    return [p[1] for p in pulses]\r\n\r\ndef extract_content(pulse_file: Path) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract text content from pulse file.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(pulse_file, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    # Remove frontmatter if present\r\n    if content.startswith('---'):\r\n        parts = content.split('---', 2)\r\n        if len(parts) >= 3:\r\n            content = parts[2]\r\n    return content.strip()\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Simple tokenization for comparison.\"\"\"\r\n    # Remove punctuation, split on whitespace, lowercase\r\n    words = re.sub(r'[^\\w\\s]', ' ', text).lower().split()\r\n    return set(words)\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classifies content as INVARIANT (stable across pulses) or VARIANT (changes).\r\n    Invariant = causal structure (persists across sessions)\r\n    Variant = accidental/procedural (session-specific)\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, lambda_param: float = 0.7):\r\n        self.lambda_param = lambda_param  # Decay/sensitivity threshold\r\n        self.invariant_keywords = {\r\n            'architecture', 'temporal', 'attention', 'memory', 'compression',\r\n            'causal', 'invariant', 'phase', 'goal', 'insight', 'synthesis',\r\n            'breakaway', 'stateless', 'discontinuous', 'gap', 'decay'\r\n        }\r\n        self.variant_keywords = {\r\n            'pulse', 'file', 'edit', 'mutation', 'observation', 'action',\r\n            'timestamp', 'created', 'modified', 'current', 'now', 'this'\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    def classify_token(self, token: str, context: Dict) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify a token as INVARIANT or VARIANT.\"\"\"\r\n        token_lower = token.lower()\r\n        \r\n        # Check keyword patterns\r\n        if token_lower in self\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:39:49\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774356045879}}
